US Secretary of State Rex Tillerson arrived in Nairobi on Friday ahead of talks with President Uhuru Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga. Among the key issues expected to be addressed during the meetings includeÂ counter terrorism; peace and security; good governance; trade and investment. Tillerson is also expected to speak on how Kenya in partnership with other Africa countries can keep their resources and benefit from them. The US envoy kicked off his inaugural tour of the continent on Tuesday in Addis Ababa Ethiopia. He held talks with the country's leadership and African Union Commission officials. Tilerson is expected to visit Chad, Djibouti and Nigeria in the coming days during his visit that ends next on March 13. His arrival followed after Uhuru and Raila agreed to work together towards healing divisions arising from last year's general elections. They told Kenyans they had set their differences aside and would work to unite the public. The
two met at Harambee House office of the President before addressing the
press. They neither specified their strategies nor took any questions. Raila,
who was first to speak, noted ethnic division came to an end today and
that he and his 'brother' will bridge the existing gap. Kenya
has faced tumultuous times since the disputed August 8, 2018
presidential election, whose outcome Raila objected and termed Uhuru an
illegitimate President. Read: New dawn: Uhuru and Raila resolve to work together to heal Kenya Click here for the latest political news   